#eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - KwaZulu-Natal Premier, Sihle Zikalala, says the province's economy is showing signs of improvement. He's been leading 'Operation Siyahlola' to assess progress in rebuilding the province after the violent looting and unrest a year ago. The unrest caused mass infrastructure damage, forcing businesses to close and increasing unemployment. 2021 July Unrest | Around 5,000 arrested, most not prosecuted or withdrawn A year after businesses and shopping centres were looted in KwaZulu-Natal, some have not recovered at all. Zikalala says damages in the manufacturing industry have contributed greatly to job losses. An oil refinery responsible for 35% of the country's fuel supply, also temporarily closed down due to the unrest. Watch the video above for more details. 